      "writtenOn": "2019-09-17T19:46:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It seems overly constraining to force these to be pointers when the only real constraint here is  they have a copy constructor and operator[]. I suppose this is so SkZip can be templated on the value types instead of templated on the iterator types the constructor would need to take. I suppose taking more than pointers would mean making the constructor of SkZip something like\n\ntemplate \u003ctypename... Its,\n          typename \u003d std::enable_if\u003cstd::is_same\u003cstd::tuple\u003cdecltype(std::declval\u003cIts\u003e()[0])...\u003e, ReturnTuple\u003e, void\u003e\u003e SkZip(size_t size, Its... its)\n\nSo the constructor takes a bunch of things with operator[] (may just be pointers) which return the right types. Then store a copy of those operator[] things and use.",
